The paper deals with a machine learning problem of bipartite ranking, which is a subfield of supervised learning. The paper discusses the use of proper (composite) losses to obtain surrogate regret bounds for bipartite ranking. This topic falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
